                        <section id="section-4">
                            <div class="container">
                                <h1>Part 4: Fire Preparedness and Safety Measures</h1>
                                <p>Being prepared for a fire can significantly reduce the risks to life and property. This section provides essential guidelines and safety measures to help individuals and communities prepare for, survive, and recover from fires.</p>
                        
                                <h2>Before a Fire: Preparation</h2>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Install smoke alarms on every level of your home, inside bedrooms and outside sleeping areas.</li>
                                    <li>Test smoke alarms every month and replace batteries at least once a year.</li>
                                    <li>Have a fire escape plan that includes two ways out of every room and an outside meeting place.</li>
                                    <li>Keep fire extinguishers in key locations and ensure everyone knows how to use them.</li>
                                </ul>
                        
                                <h2>During a Fire: Safety Actions</h2>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>If a fire occurs, get out, stay out, and call for help. Do not go back inside for anything or anyone.</li>
                                    <li>Crawl low under any smoke to your exit - heavy smoke and poisonous gases collect first along the ceiling.</li>
                                    <li>If you encounter smoke when using your primary exit, use an alternative way out.</li>
                                    <li>If you are trapped, seal the room and cover vents and cracks around doors with cloth or tape to keep smoke out.</li>
                                </ul>
                        
                                <h2>After a Fire: Recovery and Safety</h2>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Once you are out, stay out. Firefighters will assist in saving your possessions.</li>
                                    <li>If you are told to evacuate, do so immediately.</li>
                                    <li>Check yourself and family members for injuries and get medical attention if necessary.</li>
                                    <li>Listen to news updates for information about the fire and any evacuation orders.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        
                        
                        <section id="section-5">
                            <div class="container">
                                <h1>Part 5: The Role of Technology in Fire Detection and Response</h1>
                                <p>Advancements in technology have significantly impacted our ability to detect and respond to fires. From early warning systems to post-fire recovery efforts, technology plays a crucial role in minimizing the impact of fires on lives and property.</p>
                        
                                <h2>Fire Detection and Alarm Systems</h2>
                                <p>Modern smoke detectors and fire alarm systems use advanced sensors to detect fire and smoke at the earliest stages, providing crucial time for evacuation.</p>
                        
                                <h2>Remote Sensing and Drones</h2>
                                <p>Drones and satellite technology provide real-time imagery and data to monitor wildfire spread, helping to allocate firefighting resources more effectively.</p>
                        
                                <h2>Post-Fire Assessment and Recovery</h2>
                                <p>Technology aids in assessing damage, identifying the fire's cause, and planning reconstruction. Mobile apps and online platforms facilitate aid distribution and community support.</p>
                            </div>
